name: Lea Tillman
text:
I like Maxwell Airforce Base! I do my shopping there. Get my meds, go to the exchange.

The reason I'm only giving 3 Star's, is because the Base used to look so nice! Now it's just not maintained at all! What happened? It's like Maxwell Gunter Air Force Base have lost there  pride. They just don care anymore. The grass is so high, looks so shabby!
This is not the only Base I seen in this condition! it's so Sad to see.
They just don't care anymore! No Pride!

name: Del Chick
text:
I would say that this commissary could use updating BUT MOREOVER, need some customer service skills big time. However, there are two outstanding cashiers, Hunter and Pam. They both are Great, helpful with impeccable people skills!  As far as the others they need training, especially if they’re going to be talking to military families like they do!

The food court has a lot to be desired! The staff seems so unhappy for some reason!

The clinic is very pretty inside, spacious, but the pharmacy has been a thorn of contention for the six years that we’ve been getting our meds there. I’ve voiced my complaints several times, nothing seems to change. There is no reason you should ever have to wait in those lines.

name: Heather Conley
text: I need the street address to get to the main gate. Maps is taking me to closed Gates and down dirt back roads

name: Frederick Lancia
text: Major CHAD BRANDL took time to respond to my request for military records which is greatly appreciated.

name: sherry lawrence
text:
Building nice, clean, and orderly. Worn shoes need to be replaced as well shoes strings. A  easy inexpensive fix would be replacing shoe strings.
Snack bar attendant was not very pleasant, when she did speak!

name: Benjamin Royer
text: Visited family while they were temporarily stationed here. Nice base. Very quiet on the weekends. Dogs enjoyed the aircraft positioned throughout the base. America!

name: Record America
text: Master Sergeant Ables respected constitutional rights when recently tested by citizens.

name: John Marcinkevich
text: The center of activities for Air Force Advanced Education

name: Chris Murray
text: I was born there, on December 27, 1968.

name: Michael Aschinger
text: Professional education in a professional environment. Can't beat it.

name: Ty Prowant
text: The best class I have ever had the opportunity to go to was here. Great staff and convinces.

name: Sassidy 44
text: It was a great to attend protocol school here!

name: Andre Firefighter Young
text: School and training center

name: Antoine F Smith, II
text: Wonderful staff, helped me find everything I needed. Even told me if it fit right.

name: Tori W
text: Dropping off items here is very easy, especially if you live on Maxwell. There is a she'd by their door if you need to drop off an item after hours. We've personally donated lots of items that are in great condition, but just don't need.

name: Lacey Inauen
text: Used to be a lot better 4 years ago before the original owner passed away and the msgt that was running it after hadn't retired.

name: adrian purdy
text: Friendly volunteers. Great service.

name: Tyler Foster
text: Friendly staff and nice selection.

name: Brett
text: Great place and had a food pantry

name: Seth Mags
text: The hub for culture and language education, innovation, and collaboration. Great place doing great things for the Air Force and it's partners!
